160+          170 with Lies Dance on the Breeze

1014.name: Saber
1014.playstyle:
She gives herself 20% CRIT Rate in battle, so her pre-battle threshold is 80%.
If Sunday or RMC are in use, then the threshold can be lowered by another 20/10% respectively.
Saber necessitates some form of Energy Regen through other characters, so her premium teammate is Sunday as he provides extra actions for stacking Core Resonance too.

1015.name: Archer
1015.playstyle:
Sparkle is not a necessity for him to function (this is a common misconception), however she is really nice to have.

The 3rd team member will depend on matchup:
Non quantum-weak - Silver Wolf is absolutely best in slot.
Other times will depend on matchup, investment and player skill.
E.g. SW defence shred could beat out Cipher's amp if the matchup is not desired.
Or Tribbie's Follow-Ups could be valuable to trigger Archer's FUA for SP, however this is optimisation dependent.
In general, SW > Cipher > Tribbie, unless Tribbie is E1, in which case Tribbie > Cipher.

The other great option is RMC as Archer has a ultimate cost greater than that of 200 energy and hence he benefits the most from RMC's True Damage amp, as well as the 10% Crit Rate.

The last team member will be DHPT or Gallagher if you decide to run a sustain, as no other sustains are as comfortable while being SP positive.
If going 0 sustain, then any of the other options work well.

stats.Speed: Base Speed in Hyprspeed setup / 134+ Speed when you play Jing Yuan with Sunday in the -1 Speed setup

stats.BaseSpeed: 135+          SPD should be higher than Kafka's
As much as is needed to outspeed all DPS characters and even more than this if desired.
stats.StatusProbabilityBase: 140%+ (More can be useful against 40%+ Resistant enemies)

stats.BaseSpeed: 134+ (To hit MoC Cycle breakpoint without buffs - with some Speed buffs, you can build less)
stats.Attack: 2700 - 3300+ (depending on whether you're using SPD or ATK% Boots)

1222.name: Lingsha
1222.playstyle:
Lingsha is a generally good healer.

Please note, on the relic sets Lingsha can use 4pc Cavalry, Talia, Daythunder or any mix of 2pc 2pc Speed, Break Effect or Healing Bonus.

If using Iron Cavalry, please aim for 250% Break Effect
If using Talia set, please aim for 145 SPD.
Forge is used if The Dahlia is in use.
Best in Slot sustain for Break teams, even though they are often ran sustainless.
Is a competent Fire DPS, given you have the other components of a Break team.

stats.BaseSpeed: Enough Speed to ensure Moze moves first in combat and doesn't return from off-field after a large number of ally actions.
123+ (Equivalent to 134 in combat) / 133+ (Equivalent to 145 in combat for Talia)

1225.name: Fugue
1225.playstyle:
Break Effect: 220%+ (During Combat)
Speed: As fast as reasonable

Enables breaking twice.
Massive for Boothill, as most of his damage is through actual break, and Rappa, who gets double the charges.
Break necessitates The Dahlia, and hence is why Forge is viable on her.

stats.BaseSpeed: Any Speed Breakpoint          145 if using Talia
160 for Fast Sparkle          134 for Slow Sparkle
135 - 160          SPD should be higher than Kafka's

1308.name: Acheron
1308.playstyle:
Her E2 removes the need for 2 additional Nihility characters, so she can use a Harmony unit without losing the bonus damage.
Before E2, consider using 2 other Nihility characters.

Generally struggles off-element or against high-HP single target fights.

When using Preservation Characters with Acheron, you may find it useful to equip them with the “Trend of the Universal Market” light cone, as it can generate Slashed Dream every time said character gets hit.

1310.name: Firefly
1310.playstyle:
The 360%+ Break Effect threshold is only during combat.

The Dahlia is necessary for Firefly to function properly now.
Speedtuning depends on what sources of speed and advance you have. You want her to take a turn right after her ultimate state ends.

Break loses out on a lot by not going 0 sustain, so it is recommended to forgo a sustain if possible. Enemies get broken and stay broken for a long time, so dying is rare.

1313.name: Sunday
1313.playstyle:
## Where to use?
Generally speaking, Sunday is an extremely flexible unit built for Hypercarry teams, especially those that involve a summon.
The exceptions to this rule are Castorice and Evernight, as their Memosprites cannot retain the buff provided from Sunday consistently, as they repeatedly need to be respawned.


## Synergy with DHPT
With the addition of Dan Heng • Permansor Terrae, you can get the extra 50% DMG bonus from Sunday with any DPS of your choice, given Sunday and DHPT are reasonable choices.
This is especially true in the case of ATK scaling Hypercarry DPSes. The main examples of which being Aglaea, Archer, Phainon and edge cases such as E2 Acheron, DHIl or a highly optimised Feixiao.


## Builds
There are 2 play/build styles for Sunday as follows:
**Hyperspeed**
Build Sunday as fast as you can to maximize how many turns your DPS can get.
Generally SPD > 160.

**-1 SPD**
SPD-Tune Sunday to have one less SPD than your DPS to basically get a double action.
Useful for stacking mechanics or for extra damage windows.
Generally the DPS will be 135 SPD, and Sunday at 134.
Changes depending on character and sources of advance.

1315.name: Boothill
1315.playstyle:
Like Firefly and Rappa, Boothill has become relevant again due to Dahlia's release, and hence **The Dahlia is a necessity for Boothill**.
Again, because of Dahlia, Boothill is able to run Forge of the Kalpagni Lantern. This is his BiS Planar Set, however only if he is paired with Dahlia. Otherwise Talia, Kingdom of Banditry is your best bet. 

Boothill's BiS teams necessitate The Dahlia and Fugue because of their buffs and Fugue for his ramp up.
The last slot is flexible - it can be a sustain, an advancer, or a buffer.

While most of Boothill's DMG comes from his Basic Attack, the actual multipliers and DMG amplification comes from his Talent and the number of Pocket Trickshot he has. Fugue in particular allows him to gain all 3 stacks at once if you can break both the Weakness Bar, Fugue's Cloudflame Luster Bar, and kill the enemy. Regardless, she will make Pocket Trickshot generation much faster.

For Eidolon/Signature Priority, pull for his E1 then his S1, as the ramp-up increase from the E1 is much more important than the damage from S1, as the alternatives are very good,


## Teammate TL;DR: 
Necessary: The Dahlia
Nice to have: Fugue
Lower priority: HMC and Ruan Mei
Niche use cases: Bronya and Sunday

1317.name: Rappa
1317.playstyle:
ATK: 3200+ during combat
Break Effect: 250%+ during combat for the relic set
SPD: As fast as possible without compromising too mush Break Effect

Every break carry now wants The Dahlia so she will be featured everywhere, and also is why Forge is the best planar, as The Dahlia implants fire.
Fugue doubles her Charge generation for extra damage so she will be a big upgrade.
Her S1 is also miles better than any other option, hence why there aren't many options otherwise.

1321.name: The Dahlia
1321.playstyle:
The Dahlia allows Super Break damage before the enemy is Toughness Broken.
Necessary for every break carry.
Also gives 50% Weakness Break Efficiency, a lot of Break Effect, implants weakness of main carry after Ultimate, applies DEF shred, and recovers a lot of SP.
Her 3rd trace gives 30% speed to her Dance Partner when they apply weakness.
After the Dance Partner attacks, Dahlia will unleash her FuA, dealing decent dmg and recovering a skill point every other turn.

1401.name: The Herta

stats.BaseSpeed: Base Speed (With Hyperspeed Action Advancer or 4P Mourning Collapse)   |   134 Speed (Generic Endgame Breakpoint)   |   160 Speed (Higher Endgame Speed Breakpoint)   |   Also worth mentioning is that Jade, one of The Herta's more powerful teammates, will grant her 30 Speed which also needs to be taken into account.

1401.playstyle:
Is The Herta Worth Building?
The Herta is an Erudition DPS that can perform extremely well across all general and Endgame content, especially when up against five enemies. She also has the nifty ability to locate Treasure Chests around the map.

If you already have a lot of limited Erudition units in your collection, The Herta isn't a must-pull. However, The Herta can synergize well with your other Erudition units, and pulling for her will still be worth it.


Should I Get The Herta's Light Cone?
The Herta's signature Light Cone, Into the Unreachable Veil, is a quality of life upgrade for her. Into the Unreachable Veil provides a lot of Skill DMG bonus and restores a Skill Point whenever The Herta uses an Ultimate.

While a great Light Cone to have, should you choose not to get Into the Unreachable Veil, The Herta can make do with other Light Cones such as Today Is Another Peaceful Day and Geniuses' Repose.


The Herta Gameplay Guide


Talent Increases DMG Based on Interpretation:
While The Herta is on your team, enemies will receive Interpretation stacks whenever they are attacked, up to a cap of 42. Each stack of Interpretation increases the damage the targets take.

If there is another Erudition character in a team with The Herta, enemies take even more damage.


Restore Energy with Allied Attacks:
The Herta can have her energy restored through allies attacking enemies. The more enemies each ally has hit, the more energy The Herta receives.

With this in mind, units that attack frequently and can attack all enemies are best used with The Herta.


Ultimate Redistributes Interpretation Stacks:
When The Herta uses her Ultimate, she deals Ice damage to all enemies, while also redistributing all Interpretation stacks. More powerful enemies will receive more stacks of Interpretation.

After using The Herta's Ultimate, she will gain an Inspiration stack, which enhances her next Skill.


Skill Deals DMG Based on Interpretation:
When The Herta uses her Skill, she will deal damage to her target and adjacent enemies.

Additionally, if she uses has an Inspiration stack, her Skill will deal additional damage based on the number of Interpretation stacks on the primary target. The primary target's Interpretation stacks will then reset.


Technique Marks Chests on the Map:
When Herta uses her Technique, any undiscovered Chests on the map will be marked.

Additionally, when used in the Simulated Universe or Divergent Universe, The Herta will deal damage to all enemies at the start of each wave. This damage is based on a percentage of their Max HP.

1402.name: Aglaea
1402.playstyle:
Desperately wants her premium team (Sunday Cyrene) or her E1 to keep up with her steep energy demands.
SPD or ATK boots depends on how you want to speedtune her. It is difficult to give a definitive 'you should do this' for Aglaea, as it depends on your playstyle, investment and speed on other characters. I would recommend experimenting and see what works.
With E1 and her premium team, she can switch off ERR rope and go to ATK.

1403.name: Tribbie
1403.playstyle:
Tribbie is one of the best generalist buffers in the game, with her permanent 24% RES PEN, 30% Vulnerability and +2 SP every 3 turns at E0S0.
Her E1 is also one of the most versatile and worthwhile in the game, concentrating damage onto the highest enemy target.


There are 2 builds to her:

Sub-DPS:
Use the Poet of Mourning Collapse set and remember to avoid SPD substats to stay under 95 for the 32% CRIT Rate.
Use the Bone Collector planar set, aim for 5k HP.
Crit Rate: 80%+ (during combat)

Support and SP Generator:
Use the Eagle set or stick with Poet. You can generally ignore damage subs and aim with SPD or HP.
Can use Vonwaq or Lukasha planar ornaments. If the former, then make sure you get 120+ SPD.

1404.name: Mydei
1404.playstyle:
Can run 0 sustain comfortably due to his taunt and high agro value.
8k HP pre-combat is the ideal stat goal, however it is difficult and not mandatory.
Hyacine poses some level of anti-synergy with Mydei, as she reduces the amount of charge he gets after taking damage. However, the Cyrene stacking makes it worth it.
Alternatively, remove Hyacine entirely and replace her with Cerydra or Silver Wolf or any generalist.
He is difficult to pilot and requires knowledge about enemy mechanics and matchups.

1405.name: Anaxa
1405.playstyle:
If playing Hypercarry Anaxa (no other Erudition unit), don't stress over crit dmg as he gain 140% from his Trace

The ornament set "Izumo Gensei and Takama Divine Realm" just works when playing with another erudition, it doesn't work with Hypercarry Anaxa

Just consider "Eagle of Twilight Line" relic set if played with The Herta, use "Genius of Brilliant Stars" if you want Hypercarry Anaxa

1407.name: Castorice
1407.playstyle:
# Outline and Risks
- One of the best DPS units to have
- Can brute force a lot of content
- Heavily relies on her Premium team (specifically Hyacine)
- Need to invest into her whole team - generally expensive unit, as she does also want her S1

# Premium Team Sidegrades
- Castorice and Hyacine will always be there
- The other 2 units are slightly flexible - generally will be 2 of Evernight, Cyrene, Tribbie or RMC

Addressing Hyacine
- Absolute necessity - Castorice struggles to function without Hyacine's sustain and immense healing output to charge Netherwing.
- Provides a large amount of damage through her memosprite (even more damage when paired with Evernight)
- Provides a Max HP buff to the team to increase Cas' damage further.

# Pull Recommendation
- Pull if you intend to invest into her premium team (her S1, Hyacine and Evernight specifically)
- Be aware she will not perform nearly as well without her premium team
- Be aware Evernight is often times a better main dps carry than Castorice, due to her being able to 0 sustain and lacking some of the issues Castorice has, such as struggling in Single Target.

1408.name: Phainon
1408.playstyle:
Phainon is the currently one of the strongest DPSes in the game.
He wants some level of investment, but his options are very wide.
Sunday and Cerydra form the core of his premium team, with the last slot being flexible for a sustain (DHPT) or any other buffer (RMC, Tribbie, Bronya etc).
He wants to be paired with characters that grant potent buffs or can target him to generate Coreflame.
In general, his best teams have no sustain, however between Sunday's Summon damage bonus and Phainon's sustain trace, DHPT makes for a very competitive 4th slot and gives comfort for multiple ult rotations without dying.
His E2 is currently the strongest E2 in the game and takes precedence over any other investment for Phainon, other than comfort picks like Sunday and Cerydra.

1409.name: Hyacine
1409.playstyle:
Hyacine is a healer that is best suited for HP-Scalers but does such good damage and AOE that she is good everywhere.
Necessary for Castorice to function properly, and is the only viable sustain for Evernight.

Speed: 200+ should be during combat
HP: 4500+ outside combat

1410.name: Hysilens
1410.playstyle:
Should I Pull for Hysilens?
Hysilens is one of the best DoT units to be released in the game. Her ability to debuff enemies and deal DoT DMG makes her a great upgrade for DoT teams.

That being said, we only recommend getting Hysilens if you also have, or are planning to pull for Kafka to deal the most damage possible. Without Kafka, Hysilens cannot contend with other high tier units.


Should I Pull for Hysilens' Light Cone?
Hysilens' Light Cone, Why Does the Ocean Sing, provides Effect Hit Rate and can increase the enemy's DMG received from DoTs. This also provides a SPD increase that can be used by other allies when they attack an enemy.

While this is Hysilens' best-in-slot Light COne, you can consider skipping this for other Light Cones like Eyes of the Prey or any other DoT-related Light Cone. Instead, we recommend getting her E1 as this provides a better DMG increase for Hysilens.


Hysilens Gameplay Guide

Talent Inflicts Random DoTs:
When Hysilens uses her Basic ATK, Skill, or Ultimate, she can inflict different DoTs onto enemies.


Skill Increases DMG Taken by Enemies:
Hysilen's Skill deals AoE DMG and increases the DMG taken by enemies.


Ultimate Unleashes a Zone that Reduces DEF:
Hysilens' Ultimate summons a Zone and deals DMG to all enemies.

Enemies in Hysilens' Zone will have reduced DEF and take more Physical DoT DMG from Hysilens whenever they get hit by DoTs.

Technique Prevents Enemy Attacks:
Hysilens Technique summons a Dimension that will prevent enemies from attacking you.

When Hysilens attacks enemies affected by her Technique, her Talent will trigger multiple times and randomly applying DoTs to enemies.

1412.name: Cerydra
1412.playstyle:
## Use Cases
Has niche uses, but where she is used she is REALLY good.
Part of Phainon, Anaxa and Mydei premium teams.
Synergises with Cyrene in the latter 2 teams, due to being a Chrysos Heir.
Gives 20 SPD to the carry, so you will be able to forgo SPD boots on them.
Has light synergy with The Herta if she is E1 or above, otherwise do not bother with this.

# Stat Goals:
Generally 160+ SPD will be the ideal case.
Lower is fine with Wind Set or DDD advances.
Want her to be faster than your carry by a decent margin.
4k ATK is to get as much ATK buff onto the main carry as possible. Does not matter in the case of Mydei.

# Playstyle:
Stack Merit onto the DPS for their big hard hitting skills (Phainon meteor, Anaxa buffed by Cyrene, Mydei Godslayer) to be done twice in succession.
Has notable synergy with Anaxa due to him being able to stack her extremely quickly.
It is a good idea to save your Ultimate to make sure you time the double skill to be for these important skills listed above.

1413.name: Evernight
1413.playstyle:
Should You Pull for Evernight?

Evernight is a Remembrance unit that is a DPS that can also buff other Memosprites. She can deal damage to all enemies and provides CRIT DMG buffs geared toward Memosprites.



With her Memosprite buffs being a key feature, Evernight works best with other Remembrance units, with Castorice benefiting the most from her kit. If you main Castorice and want her to be stronger or are in need of an Ice DPS, Evernight is worth pulling for!



Should You Pulll for Evernight's Light Cone?

To Evernight's Stars is designed for Evernight for its HP stat and Energy Regen. This enhances Evernight's support capabilities since it helps other Memosprites deal more damage to enemies.



While nice to have, you can use The Flower Remembers or Sweat Now, Cry Less as cheaper alternative options. You can also use The Story's Next Page or Victory in a Blink simply as stat sticks.



Evernight Build

Evernight is best built as a DPS unit that can also provide support to the party. World-Remaking Deliverer and Bone Collection's Serene Demesne are Evernight's best relics for the party-wide DMG buff and HP stats.



Prioritize CRIT DMG on Evernight since her buffs scale on that stat, and she can get the CRIT Rate from her Dark the Night, Still the Moon Bonus Ability and Trace Nodes. Since Evernight's Memosprite already has a Base SPD of 160, it is unnecessary to build SPD for this character.



Is a Memosprite Buffer

Evernight can increase Memosprite CRIT DMG when she is in the party. This buff becomes stronger the more ally memosprites there are on the field.



This makes Evernight a great Support for Remembrance units!



Accumulate Memoria Stacks with Skill

Evernight's Skill will summon Evey; her Memosprite. Evernight will also gain Memoria stacks through her Skill, which increases the damage dealt by Evey.



After collecting enough Memoria stacks, Evey will take action and deal damage to all enemies.



Gain Memoria by Losing HP

When Evernight or Evey loses HP, Memoria stacks will be accumulated.



Enter an Enhanced State with Ultimate

Evernight's Ultimate can deal DMG to all enemies and both her and Evey will enter an Enhanced State called the Darkest Riddle.



During Darkest Riddle, Evernight and Evey can deal increased damage and the Skill will be enhanced to gain Extra Memoria stacks.



Increase Ally CRIT DMG with Technique

Evernight's Technique increases the CRIT DMG of all ally memosprites and gain extra Memoria stacks at the start of combat.

1414.name: Dan Heng • Permansor Terrae
1414.playstyle:
• Can stack Sacerdos with his skill.
• Sunday advances Souldragon and gives Bondmate an extra 50% damage boost.
• Bondmate is able to use The Wondrous BananAmusement Park.
• Can be SP Positive.
• Works well with most ATK scalers.
• Dragon does not disappear when Phainon enters ultimate, given he is the bondmate.
Ideally 160+ SPD.

1415.name: Cyrene
1415.playstyle:
## **Cyrene: Character Synergies & Team Compositions**

### **Hyacine**

* **Best For:** Fast Ultimate charging.
* **Synergy:** Hyacine reaches high **SPD** naturally, and her actions are followed by Little Ica for 2 Recollection stacks.
* **Key Buff:** After Cyrene's Ultimate, Hyacine gains **"Ode to Sky"** automatically. This increases the healing tally rate for Little Ica's Memosprite Skill DMG.

### **Aglaea**

* **Best For:** Energy restoration and Memosprite stacking.
* **Synergy:** Cyrene instantly maxes Aglaea's Memosprite Talent.
* **Note:** This is most useful if Aglaea exits her Supreme Stance. Cyrene can also restore **70 Energy** to help mitigate Aglaea’s high costs.

### **Mydei**

* **Best For:** Burst damage on demand.
* **Synergy:** Every Cyrene Ultimate triggers Mydei’s **"Godslayer Be Gods"** attack and provides a massive **CRIT DMG** boost.
* **Benefit:** Mydei becomes less dependent on HP loss, as you can time Cyrene’s Ultimate to trigger his strongest abilities.

### **Tribbie**

* **Best For:** Early battle momentum.
* **Synergy:** As a Chrysos Heir, she increases Cyrene’s Ultimate stacks at the start of battle.
* **Note:** Cyrene’s buffs for Tribbie only apply to Tribbie herself; generally, it is better to target other allies unless no better options exist.

### **Castorice**

* **Best For:** Single-target (ST) nuking and HP mirroring.
* **Synergy:** Cyrene’s Memosprite mirrors Cyrene’s HP fluctuations, generating **Newbuds** for Castorice.
* **Overcharge Mechanic:** Allows Castorice to overcharge her Ultimate up to **200%**.
* **Single-Target:** Increases Bounce DMG from 40% to **112%** at max overflow.
* **Multi-Target:** Overcharging is *not* recommended here, as overflow doesn't benefit Netherwing’s Breath attacks.



### **Anaxa**

* **Best For:** Main DPS Erudition builds.
* **Synergy:** Cyrene's Ultimate grants Anaxa an **immediate action**, a Skill Point, and extra Skill Bounce instances (which Cerydra can duplicate).
* **Bonus:** Also provides a large Skill DMG increase for other Erudition allies on the team.

### **Cipher**

* **Best For:** Amplifying DEF shred.
* **Synergy:** Increases Cipher's DEF reduction on primary/secondary targets by **20%/12%**.
* **Note:** Usually outperformed by the repeatable effects of Mydei or Anaxa.

### **Phainon**

* **Best For:** Infinite Ultimate uptime.
* **Synergy:** Allows Phainon to stay in his Ultimate state indefinitely, refreshing **Extra Turns** and recovering Scourge.
* **Bonus:** Adds minor Fire DMG instances and CRIT buffs to his attacks.

### **Hysilens**

* **Best For:** DoT detonation and AOE coverage.
* **Synergy:** Provides a **120% DMG boost** and allows Hysilens to detonate DoTs via Basic ATK/Skill.
* **Utility:** Re-applying the buff regenerates **60 Energy** and recovers Skill Points.

### **Cerydra**

* **Synergy:** Reduces the hits required for **Coup de Main** from 6 to 5 and grants **30% CRIT DMG** to the target.

### **March 7th • Evernight**

* **Synergy:** A permanent buff improves **CRIT DMG scaling by 12%**, increases Memoria generation, and boosts Memosprite Skill DMG. Perfect for reinforcing mono-Remembrance teams.

### **Dan Heng • Permansor Terrae**

* **Synergy:** Permansor Terrae gains **24% Bondmate DMG** and additional multipliers without needing to be actively targeted.
* **Emergency Utility:** Using Cyrene’s Memosprite Skill on him triggers an emergency **Follow-up ATK and Shield**.
